$interpreted: Soohyeon: Meong Sa, are you alright!? You're hurt...
Meong Sa: I'm fine... ugh...
Soohyeon: I don't hear the guards anymore, we might have lost them. Let's rest up here for a second.
Soohyeon: We'll bandage your wounds once we meet up with Li Hwa again.
Soohyeon: It's okay, don't cry~
Meong Sa: I'm sure this has all given him a good scare... Could you walk around with him for a bit? Calm him down?
Soohyeon: Walk around? Uh... like this?
Soohyeon: Ah, he's not crying anymore~
Soohyeon: Hehe, mothers know best, I guess.
Meong Sa: I haven't held him for so long...
Meong Sa: What I wouldn't give just to hold him one more time...
Soohyeon: Don't worry, once Li Hwa finds a cure, you'll be able to be together again!
Soohyeon: Come a little closer. See, he knows his mother's near. Look at him smile~
Meong Sa: But... I...
Soohyeon: It's okay, I'll hold him.
Soohyeon: Just watch him.
Maeok: Soohyeon!!!
Soohyeon: Wha...
Maeok: Soohyeon! Are you alright? Did that bewitcher touch you!?
Soohyeon: Mom... I....
Maeok: I heard you were threatened by one of them, and I got so scared...
Maeok: I'm so happy you're alright! Oh, my child...
Soohyeon: (Is mom... crying? I think this is the first time I've ever seen her cry...)
Serious Guard: Arbiter! The info we got from that seahorse was suspicious, to say the least. Kept sending us in circles!
Weak Seahorse: Ah... ah...
Weak Seahorse: Meong Sa!
Serious Guard: Stop right there!
Weak Seahorse: So much blood... Please don't die... please... don't leave me...
Meong Sa: Stupid...
Meong Sa: You can't... touch me...
Weak Seahorse: Please... no...
Maeok: He's been bewitched!!
Weak Seahorse: Aaaaaaaaaaagghhh!!!
Maeok: Soohyeon! Run!!!
Soohyeon: Mom!!!
Soohyeon: Don't hurt my mom!!!
Soohyeon: Mom! Are you alright!?
Soohyeon: Mom!!!
Maeok: You're too nice for your own good, you know that? It'll come back to bite you one day!
Soohyeon: But mom... the bewitchers are innocent. They never asked to be that way!
Soohyeon: Why do you have to kill them...
Maeok: Why!? Look around you! Isn't it obvious!?
Maeok: We're not lucky enough to be able to protect everyone all of the time! I have to make some sacrifices!
Maeok: To protect the alliance, the public, and my only daughter!
Soohyeon: ......
Soohyeon: Mom...
Li Hwa: Don't worry, I'll have a friend take care of the child.
Li Hwa: Us jellyfish live for quite a long time, so taking care of children every once in a while is a nice little treat.
Soohyeon: Thank you...
Li Hwa: Don't take things so hard, Soohyeon. I'll worry about you...
Soohyeon: But everything's my fault... I knew it was dangerous, but I still let her do it.
Soohyeon: And... if I could have stopped her husband...
Soohyeon: Ow!!
Li Hwa: I know... I feel terrible about Meong Sa and her husband...
Li Hwa: But it's because life is so fragile, so fleeting, that we can't waste time beating ourselves up about it.
Soohyeon: But, I'm so useless... I couldn't do anything to help...
Li Hwa: You're not useless!
Li Hwa: You're the one who figured out how to use the celestial net, remember? You've helped so much with my research!
Li Hwa: And...
Li Hwa: Even if you can't see it right now...
Li Hwa: I just know you're going to do so many more great things! Things that only you can do!
Soohyeon: Things that... only I can do?
Li Hwa: That's right! Things you'll figure out on your own.
Li Hwa: It's like my teacher always said, 'The search for understanding oneself is the greatest of all human endeavors.'
Soohyeon: You need to find out who you are, and what you can do.
Li Hwa: Also, I'm thinking of going back to the Rune Academy for a bit to try and find more about bewitching.
Li Hwa: So I'm going to need you to look after Pearl Palace for me. See? Without you I'd be in a huge jam...
Soohyeon: You can count on me! I'll help keep everyone safe and sound!
Yonghyeon: Kong—Soo—hyeon!!!
Yonghyeon: Where've you been!? We haven't sparred in forever!
Soohyeon: Excuse me!? Can you not tell that Miss Li Hwa and I are talking? Could you not just barge into our conversation?
Li Hwa: Oh, you've got a guest, huh? Well, I'll let you two chat, then.
Li Hwa: Remember, you're always welcome in my palace, Soohyeon~!
Yonghyeon: When'd you get to be such good friends with that old hag?
Yonghyeon: Eh, whatever. Come on, let's spar! I'm so gonna kick your butt this time!
Soohyeon: I... I never said I felt like sparring...
Soohyeon: (Something only I can do? Even though I'm a bewitcher... No, maybe it's exactly because I'm a bewitcher...)
Soohyeon: But what is it...?
Yonghyeon: You talking to yourself over there? Come on, Soohyeon...
Soohyeon: ......
Soohyeon: I said, I'll never get sick of watching you cry, no matter how many times I beat you!
Yonghyeon: Hmph! There's no way you'll be me this time!!
Soohyeon: Guess I won't know until I try~!
Soohyeon: (That's right... I won't know until I try...)
Soohyeon: (I can't give up hope... I can't quit. I need to keep going. For Li Hwa... for everyone!)
